---
/**
 * ScaleOfChains — fixed bottom-right Victorian-style scale bar.
 *
 * Lifted from legacy/Map/mushroom_green_1865_v10_11_35_28.html lines 663-687
 * (JS) / 705-715 (resolved DOM). Renders four alternating black/cream chain
 * segments with 0/1/2/3/4 ch. tick labels and a "SCALE OF CHAINS" header.
 *
 * Chain dimensions (from the source's own comment):
 *   1 chain = 20.1168 m
 *   A → C section ≈ 164 m ≈ 8.15 chains
 *   Bar shows 4 chains = 80.47 m
 *   At print scale (31 cm = 164 m), 80.47 m ≈ 15.2 cm ≈ 58 px @ 96 dpi
 *   So each chain segment = 14.5 px wide
 *
 * Note: the bar is sized in CSS pixels, NOT geo-anchored to the map. It's
 * an aesthetic Victorian flourish, accurate at the default zoom (18.25 set
 * by VillageMap), but it does NOT update on zoom — same behaviour as the
 * legacy file. Leaflet's L.control.scale would be the dynamic counterpart;
 * the source deliberately rolled its own static bar for the antique look.
 *
 * Position: bottom-right, just above the SurveyedBy attribution. Sits at
 * z-index 1400 with `pointer-events: none` so the map drag/zoom underneath
 * remains unblocked.
 *
 * Hidden on print — same logic as the title cartouche; the printed version
 * uses the legacy print header for context and the bar would clash with
 * Chromium's own print scale (if enabled).
 *
 * Trust boundary: hard-coded literals from the source. No user input.
 */
---
<div class="scale-of-chains" aria-label="Scale: 4 chains (~80 metres)">
  <div class="scale-header">SCALE OF CHAINS</div>
  <div class="scale-bar">
    <div class="seg seg-dark"></div>
    <div class="seg seg-light"></div>
    <div class="seg seg-dark"></div>
    <div class="seg seg-light"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="scale-ticks">
    <span>0</span><span>1</span><span>2</span><span>3</span><span>4 ch.</span>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .scale-of-chains {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 60px;
    right: 105px;
    z-index: 1400;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .scale-header {
    font-size: 7.5px;
    color: #3a2008;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .scale-bar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: stretch;
    border: 1px solid #4a2c08;
    height: 8px;
    width: 58px; /* 4 chains × 14.5px */
  }
  .seg {
    width: 14.5px;
  }
  .seg-dark  { background: #2c1008; }
  .seg-light { background: #f5e6c8; }
  /* Vertical hairline between segments — first segment doesn't get one. */
  .seg + .seg {
    border-left: 1px solid #4a2c08;
  }
  .scale-ticks {
    display: flex;
    font-size: 7px;
    color: #3a2008;
    width: 60px;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-top: 1px;
  }

  /* Print: hide. The legacy print layout omits this for the same reason
     as the cartouche — Chromium's own print scale is sufficient. */
  @media print {
    .scale-of-chains { display: none; }
  }
</style>
